From https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1AeeADtT0U1AukliiNyiVzVRdLYPkTbruQSk38DeutU8/edit#gid=511623409
as linked to from https://pan.ukbb.broadinstitute.org/

wget https://pan-ukb-us-east-1.s3.amazonaws.com/sumstats_flat_files/biomarkers-30840-both_sexes-irnt.tsv.bgz
wget https://pan-ukb-us-east-1.s3.amazonaws.com/sumstats_flat_files_tabix/biomarkers-30840-both_sexes-irnt.tsv.bgz.tbi

Prepping igv input:
Grab lines chr, pos, id = (chr_pos_ref_alt), pval
Remove NA pvals
Set pval 0 to 1e-300
Tabix the file

{ echo -e "chr\tpos\tsnp\tpval" ; 
 zcat biomarkers-30840-both_sexes-irnt.tsv.bgz |
 tail -n +2 | awk 'BEGIN {FS = "\t"} { print $1 "\t" $2 "\t" $1 "_" $2 "_" $3 "_" $4 "\t" $32}'
; } | grep -v NA | sed -e 's/0.000e+00/1.000e-300/' > igv.input.gwas
bgzip igv.input.gwas
tabix -S 1 -b 2 -e 2 igv.input.gwas.gz

Also extract signal regions for viewing in LocusZoom:
zcat igv.input.gwas.gz |
awk '{if ($4 <= 5e-8) { print $1 " " $2 } }' |
python -c "import sys;
  s = set((int(line.split()[0]), (int(line.strip().split()[1])//1000000)*1000000) for line in sys.stdin if line.split()[0] != 'X' and line.split()[0] != 'Y') ;
  l = sorted(s) ; [print(f'{chr}:{pos+1}-{pos+1000000}') for (chr, po s) in l]" 
> signal_regions.txt
